                  </persName>
            . As I was coming along Bevismarks,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="177209090045"></xptr> yesterday was a week, I saw the prisoner walking with a tankard under his arm; he asked a man to buy it; he asked a guinea and a half for it; the man said he would not buy it because he did not believe he came honestly by it; he went away, and I followed him; he shewed it to another man, and that man said if he came honestly by it he would give him 4 s. for it; I secured him and I gave the tankard to Marks.</p>
               <p>- Marks. Levi gave the prisoner in charge to me, and gave me this tankard; (produced and deposed to by the prosecutor.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>I put my foot against the tankard as I was coming up some steps near the Fleet-market; it was under some straw.</p>
